# TypeScript Patterns

## Types

- Core interfaces in `src/types/investment.ts`: `InvestmentYearRow`, `PensionYearRow`, `CombinedYearRow`, `MonthlySavingsTarget`
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and aliases

## Utilities

Utility functions are pure and side-effect free:

```typescript
// Good: pure function with typed return
export function getLastRow<T>(data: T[]): T {
  return data[data.length - 1];
}

// Bad: side effects in utility
export function fetchAndFormatData() { ... }
```

## Configuration

- All magic numbers live in `config/investment.config.ts`
- Derived constants (e.g. `PROJECTION_YEARS`, `ROW_INDEX_AT_40`) computed from base values
- Shared lookup arrays (e.g. `INVESTMENT_YEARS`) exported from config
